<taxonomicName id="139248A85917A63EFF0AC2E28578FE55" authority="Cash, 1904" authorityName="Cash" authorityYear="1904" box="[166,534,463,490]" class="Vampyrellidea" family="Biomyxidae" genus="Penardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Athalamida" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395917A63EFF0AC2E286FEFE55" bold="true" box="[166,400,463,490]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">Penardia mutabilis</emphasis>
Cash, 1904
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="4CA92FAE5917A63EFD89C2E2850FFE55" box="[549,609,463,490]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1804,1826]" captionTargetBox="[166,1225,1236,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-325@4.[592,1225,1236,1711]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 5. Penardia mutabilis, locomotory forms (a, b). x1240." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449229/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">fig. 5</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C8860A05917A63EFF77C122863FFBD5" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" type="description">
<paragraph id="D42D332B5917A63EFF77C12284FFFD15" blockId="4.[166,1225,527,874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">This is a large naked free-living amoeba. Cell shape is variable, spread if adhered to a substrate. The locomotion is relatively rapid. In motion, the amoeba changes its shape, branching in a reticulate net. Pseudopodia can reach 35 μm in length, growing out of a peripheral hyaline fringe of the cytoplasm. Cell length is 300–540 μm, cell width is 80– 110 μm, L/B ratio is 3.5–4. The nuclei are 5–7.5 μm in diameter.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D42D332B5917A63EFF77C18284A8FCB5" blockId="4.[166,1225,527,874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">
Remarks: the species can be distinguished from closely related species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="139248A85917A63EFF0AC1FD86CCFD55" authority="Leidy, 1875" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1875" box="[166,418,719,746]" class="Vampyrellidea" family="Biomyxidae" genus="Biomyxa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Athalamida" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395917A63EFF0AC1FD8663FD56" box="[166,269,720,745]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">Biomyxa</emphasis>
Leidy, 1875
</taxonomicName>
by cytoplasm’s rapid movement and greenish color (the 
<taxonomicName id="139248A85917A63EFBCDC1FD83A6FD56" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1875" box="[1121,1224,720,745]" class="Vampyrellidea" family="Biomyxidae" genus="Biomyxa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Athalamida" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395917A63EFBCDC1FD83A6FD56" box="[1121,1224,720,745]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">Biomyxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
amoebae have uncolored clear cytoplasm) (
<bibRefCitation id="B0034EDA5917A63EFD0EC1C284D7FCB5" author="Page, F. C. &amp; Siemensma, F. J." box="[674,953,751,778]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" pagination="3 - 170" refId="ref2346" refString="Page, F. C., Siemensma, F. J. 1991. Nackte Rhizopoda und Heliozoea (Protozoenfauna; Bd 2). Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart; New York, 3 - 170." type="book chapter" year="1991">Page, Siemensma, 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D42D332B5917A63EFF77C0228366FC95" blockId="4.[166,1225,527,874]" box="[219,1032,783,810]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">
Distribution: 
<taxonomicName id="139248A85917A63EFED7C03D8569FC96" authorityName="Cash" authorityYear="1904" box="[379,519,783,809]" class="Vampyrellidea" family="Biomyxidae" genus="Penardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Athalamida" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395917A63EFED7C03D8569FC96" box="[379,519,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">P. mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="B0034EDA5917A63EFD48C0228495FC95" author="Page, F. C. &amp; Siemensma, F. J." box="[740,1019,783,810]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" pagination="3 - 170" refId="ref2346" refString="Page, F. C., Siemensma, F. J. 1991. Nackte Rhizopoda und Heliozoea (Protozoenfauna; Bd 2). Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart; New York, 3 - 170." type="book chapter" year="1991">Page, Siemensma, 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D42D332B5917A63EFF77C0028545FCD5" blockId="4.[166,1225,527,874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">
<materialsCitation id="64FA39765917A63EFF77C0028549FCD5" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3757644302" location="lake Svitiaz" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Volyn'">
Habitats: we found the species in 
<location id="D14D65F05917A63EFDC2C002859DFCF5" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:5C3B823D5917A63EFF0AC2E2863FFBD5:D14D65F05917A63EFDC2C002859DFCF5" box="[622,755,815,842]" name="lake Svitiaz" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" stateProvince="Volyn'">lake Svitiaz</location>
(Shatsky National Natural Park, 
<collectingRegion id="1656FDC95917A63EFB2CC0028792FCD5" country="Ukraine" name="Volyn'" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">Volyn Region</collectingRegion>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="B0034EDA5917A63EFEBEC062854EFCD5" author="Patcyuk, M. K. &amp; Dovgal, I. V." box="[274,544,847,874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" pagination="355 - 360" refId="ref2629" refString="Patcyuk, M. K., Dovgal, I. V. 2012. Biotopic distribution of naked amoebes (Protista) in Ukrainian Polissya area. Vestnik Zoologii, 46 (4), 355 - 360." type="journal article" year="2012">Patcyuk, Dovgal, 2012</bibRefCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D42D332B5917A63EFF77C0A2863FFBD5" blockId="4.[166,1225,911,1130]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">
Thus, as a result of the research, 5 amoebae species were found in 
<collectingCountry id="AC8573BB5917A63EFC72C0A28350FC15" box="[990,1086,911,938]" name="Ukraine" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
for the first time. According to latest views on the system of naked amoebae (
<bibRefCitation id="B0034EDA5917A63EFC27C082831CFC75" author="Smirnov, A. V. &amp; Chao, E. &amp; Nassonova, E. S. &amp; Cavalier-Smith, T." box="[907,1138,943,970]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" pagination="545 - 570" refId="ref2889" refString="Smirnov, A. V., Chao, E., Nassonova, E. S., Cavalier-Smith, T. 2011. A Revised Classification of Naked Lobose Amoebae (Amoebozoa: Lobosa). Protistology, 162, 545 - 570." type="journal article" year="2011">Smirnov et al., 2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B0034EDA5917A63EFBD7C0828665FC55" author="Bass, D. &amp; Chao, E. &amp; Nikolaev, S." pageId="4" pageNumber="391" pagination="75 - 109" refId="ref2198" refString="Bass, D., Chao, E., Nikolaev, S. et al. 2009. Phylogeny of Novel Naked Filose and Reticulose Cercozoa: Granofilosea cl. n. and Proteomyxidea Revised. Protistogy, 160, 75 - 109." type="journal article" year="2009">Bass et al., 2009</bibRefCitation>
), they belong to 4 genera from 4 classes, 4 orders and 4 families. Four of the species are lobosea naked amoebae (
<taxonomicName id="139248A85917A63EFE56C0C285DAFBB5" box="[506,692,1007,1034]" class="Tubulinea" family="Leptomyxidae" genus="Rhizamoeba" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Leptomyxida" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395917A63EFE56C0C285E4FBB6" box="[506,650,1007,1033]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">Rhizamoeba</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="139248A85917A63EFD6DC0DD8411FBB6" baseAuthorityName="Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[705,895,1007,1033]" class="Lobosa" family="Thecamoebidae" genus="Thecamoeba" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Amoebida" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="quadrilineata">
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395917A63EFD6DC0DD8411FBB6" box="[705,895,1007,1033]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">T. quadrilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395917A63EFC21C0DD834DFBB6" box="[909,1059,1008,1033]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">
<taxonomicName id="139248A85917A63EFC21C0DD8371FBB6" baseAuthorityName="Ehrenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[909,1055,1008,1033]" class="Lobosa" family="Thecamoebidae" genus="Thecamoeba" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Amoebida" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="verrucosa">T. verrucosa</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="139248A85917A63EFB87C0C283D7FBB5" box="[1067,1209,1007,1034]" class="Lobosa" family="Hyalodiscidae" genus="Flamella" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Amoebida" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395917A63EFB87C0C283FEFBB6" box="[1067,1168,1007,1033]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">Flamella</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
), one is a naked filosea amoeba species (
<taxonomicName id="139248A85917A63EFDC4C73D859AFB96" authorityName="Cash" authorityYear="1904" box="[616,756,1039,1065]" class="Vampyrellidea" family="Biomyxidae" genus="Penardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Athalamida" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395917A63EFDC4C73D859AFB96" box="[616,756,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">P. mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Also, 
<taxonomicName id="139248A85917A63EFCE1C73D84B6FB96" authorityName="Cash" authorityYear="1904" box="[845,984,1039,1065]" class="Vampyrellidea" family="Biomyxidae" genus="Penardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Athalamida" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395917A63EFCE1C73D84B6FB96" box="[845,984,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">P. mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ecologically belongs to limnic species complex of naked amoebae that is characteristic of Shatsk lakes (
<bibRefCitation id="B0034EDA5917A63EFBCDC7028628FBD5" author="Patcyuk, M. K. &amp; Dovgal, I. V." pageId="4" pageNumber="391" pagination="355 - 360" refId="ref2629" refString="Patcyuk, M. K., Dovgal, I. V. 2012. Biotopic distribution of naked amoebes (Protista) in Ukrainian Polissya area. Vestnik Zoologii, 46 (4), 355 - 360." type="journal article" year="2012">Patcyuk, Dovgal, 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
